Problem Statement

Language barriers make communication difficult for people who do not understand foreign languages. Many existing translation tools require internet subscriptions, API keys, or complex interfaces, making them unsuitable for beginners or quick translation tasks.

There is a need for a simple, free, and user-friendly translation tool that can:

1.translate text easily
2.support multiple languages
3.detect language automatically
4.handle document/text file translation
5.provide quick results
This project aims to solve this problem by creating a Python-based translation tool using googletrans.

Scope of the Project

This project includes:

✅ Basic text translation ✅ Batch translation (multiple sentences) ✅ File translation (.txt) ✅ Automatic language detection ✅ Translation history display ✅ Listing supported languages ✅ User-friendly menu interface

The scope is limited to:

1.text-based translation only
2..txt file translation
3.internet-dependent translation using Google services
Future scope may include:

🔹 GUI interface (Tkinter) 🔹 Voice-to-text translation 🔹 PDF/doc translation 🔹 Mobile app or web version

This project is designed for:
✅ Students ✅ Teachers ✅ Travelers ✅ Content writers ✅ Programmers learning languages ✅ Researchers ✅ Anyone needing quick language translation

It is especially useful for users who:
1.want free translation
2.need simple and fast output
3.do not want to use paid APIs
4.prefer a command-line tool

High-Level Features
⭐ Supports 100+ languages ⭐ Automatic language detection ⭐ Basic and batch translation ⭐ File translation (.txt) support ⭐ Translation history storage ⭐ Menu-driven interface ⭐ No API key required ⭐ Lightweight and easy to use
